                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113 Airplanes/103: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-09T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Your 96, May 7, 3 p.m. The Department desires that you inform Beall that as
                    the proposed inquiry relates to the question of bringing about notification to
                    the Department that the Chinese Government desires that export of the airplanes
                    from the United States be authorized, the Legation is not in position to
                    interpose in a matter where the initiative and responsibility lie with the
                    Chinese Government and the interested American firm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
